<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-670-733  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 670 733.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Nov 26 1990 v219 n23 pS44(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fiber optics: the European mosaic. (telecommunication technology)(Transmission Special: Fiber Optics Explodes into the Local Loop)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Williamson, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>There is diversity in the development and deployment of fiberoptic technology in Europe because of national differencesinvolving geography, economic activities and regulatoryarrangements.andP;  There are also common elements that can beidentified in the overall mosaic.andP;  Everywhere, fiber haspenetrated first with trunk routes, has evolved junction systems,and in some places, has started to appear in the local loop.andO;Germany has one of the most ambitious installation plans.andP;  Italyand Norway are using underwater systems, running fiber down theircoastlines or across lakes.andP;  The UK plans underwater systems usingthe nation's canals.andP;  International standardization work isproceeding in Europe, and metropolitan area networks (MANs) areattracting considerable regional interest.andP;  Fiber to the home(FTTH), or at least fiber to the curb (FTTC), is the object ofmuch experimentation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     EuropeTelecommunicationsTelephone systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>